import string
punc=string.punctuation
for i in df.columns:
    if df[i].dtype=='O':
        df[i]=df[i].str.replace('['+punc+']','',regex=True)
        df[i]=df[i].astype(int)

In [11]:
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA

for i in range(1,5):
    pca=PCA(n_components=i)
    
    pca.fit(df)
    e2d=pca.transform(df)
    e2d_df=pd.DataFrame(e2d)
    print("Hence we reduced the shape of data from ",df.shape,' to ',e2d_df.shape)
    print('n_compopnent vale:',i)
    
    print('The variance ratio sum is:',pca.explained_variance_ratio_.sum())
    print('---------------------------------------------------------------------')

Hence we reduced the shape of data from  (207, 18)  to  (207, 1)

7)Plot elbow chart or scree plot to find out optimal number of clusters.
In [14]:
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
l=[]
for i in range(1,19):
    km=KMeans(n_clusters=i,init='k-means++',random_state=5)
    km.fit(new_df)
    l.append(km.inertia_)
plt.plot(range(1,19),l)
plt.grid()
plt.xticks(range(1,19))
plt.title('The Elobw Method Graph')  
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters(k)')  
plt.ylabel('Within-Cluster Sum of Square')  
plt.show()

we will consider n_clusters=3

for i in list(df.index):
    t=df.loc[i]
    X=list(t.index)
    Y=list(t.values)
    plt.title(i)
    plt.bar(X,Y)
    plt.setp(plt.gca().get_xticklabels(), rotation=90, horizontalalignment='right',color='gray') # Rotate Axis Labels
    plt.show()
